If you believe the information we have stored about you is incorrect, please contact us and we will update it. Information that we no longer use is erased on an ongoing basis. You can ask us to delete your information at any time, after any legal requirements are no longer met.
3. SECURITY OF INFORMATION
We, like so many others, use Facebook's technology for marketing ("
When you register with us by phone, email, online booking or visit, we save your contact details in order to efficiently manage your bookings or other available services with us. We send newsletters to inform you about offers and current events. You can always unsubscribe from these via a link in our newsletters. Postal mailings also occur.
On your first visit to our website, a so-called "cookie" automatically is sent to your computer. A cookie is a small text file that contains information and is stored on the visitor's computer. Cookies are used for technical reasons to enable you to use the website in the best possible way and for us to register visitor statistics. We also use Google Analytics to improve our service, ease of use and to analyze how the site is used.
When you book a hotel through an online booking agency, such as booking.com or hotels.com, you submit your personal information to them. These personal data are responsible for and handled by the respective players in accordance with their personal data policy. When a booking is completed through an OTA, they send certain personal information to the respective hotel to confirm that the booking is made.
We always handle your data reliably and we do not pass this information on to third parties. However, we may disclose your personal information to suppliers who, for example, provide IT services, media selection or advertising for our business. Recipients who handle personal data on our behalf should always enter into a so-called personal data access agreement with us, in order to ensure that your data is handled correctly and securely.
