Welcome!
Strictly over 15s only allowed at Asia Spa.
Our spa is mobile-free, apart from in the gym. When you carry your mobile with you, it is easy to focus on that instead of mindfulness and the tranquil spa experience.
Please bring underwear or dry swimwear to change into before your treatment.
Every 30 minutes, a member of our staff presents information about facilities and explains Japanese ablution, the various areas of the spa and different activities so that you can make the most of your visit at Asia Spa.
Should you wish to access the gym or participate in one of our activity classes, please bring suitable gym wear. Our activity classes are performed barefoot, but please use trainers (suitable for indoor activities) in the gym.
USEFUL INFORMATION FOR YOUR VISIT AT ASIA SPA
Let our watchwords tranquillity and harmony be your guiding star during your visit, talk in hushed tones and move slowly and mindfully around the spa.
Mobile-free spa
There are separate ablution rooms for ladies and gentlemen.
Experience Asia Spa in the best possible way
Ablution should ideally be done naked, without any swimwear.
Here you will find information about what is good to know when to visit us at Asia Spa.
If you are staying at the hotel, you can change into your yukata and slippers in the comfort of your hotel room and you wear your swimwear beneath the robe.
Should you want to give yourself a little bit of pampering with a
Start your spa visit by scrubbing, washing and showering in the Japanese-style ablution room. This ablution ritual should be done in silence and you wash all-over with a flannel, making small circular massaging motions towards the heart.
At the spa reception, you will also be given a cup, flannel and towel. These should be carried with you so that you can keep hydrated and also wipe yourself down between the different spa activities.
Our spa treatments
Asia Spa is all about letting go of the hustle and bustle of everyday life and focus inwardly, which is becoming more and more difficult as many of us are constantly connected and online. We need to pull together to make Asia Spa that special, little oasis, where you can spend some time without being influenced or affected by what is going on in the world around you. Grab your chance of escaping the external world for a moment or two.
If possible, avoid bringing valuables into the spa. There are a few safe deposit boxes in the changing rooms. Please do not wear any jewellery in the pool area, this is for your own safety.
Alcohol and mobile telephones are not allowed inside the spa facilities.
Upon arrival at Asia Spa, you will be given a yukata (Japanese bathrobe) and slippers. Yukata and slippers make up the dress code throughout the spa and that is what you should wear as you move around in the spa facilities.


